author: NotLaoDefinitely
text: A year ago, I found an animation titled "Ejected". After watching it, I clicked the link in the description, leading me here: my first viewing of Rushia. Though I never watched her streams, I still support her. And here we are now, the last hours of Rushia's channel. I have said this a lot of times and will say it until it disappears...thank you. Thank you for the memories, the jokes and the memes, the death metal and all. I pray for your safety and success in the future.

author: Random Dog
text:
She didnt even get to do anything as the impostor though lol. It gets annoying when you’re taken out less than a minute into the game without even really playing. 

Besides, she’s probably playing it up bit to be more entertaining. A cute anime girl suddenly screaming bloody murder is unexpected, so to most people it ends up being pretty funny.

author: Dimas Abiyoso
text: @Random Dog  The crewmates were lucky to vote Rushia, this might be her unlucky moment, and then her sudden rage was an act to entertain the viewers not a genuine rage?

author: Random Dog
text:
@Dimas Abiyoso  what I’m saying is her job is to be an entertainer, and she has to exaggerate for her audience. She might genuinely be annoyed, but if she was alone she might not yell and scream. Since she is streaming for a bunch people who can basically only hear her voice, she likely tries to entertain them by playing up her emotions and verbally communicating with the audience. Plenty of other streamers do it too, though they might react to things a bit differently because they’re human beings with different personalities.

Plus, she seems to stop pretty quickly and easily when needed. I know when I get pissed I’ll be seething for a while, so either she has great self control or she was playing it up a tad lol

author: Munzir Absa

Also look a few minutes after 41:27 at 42:47, she seems quite happy and able to control her anger, even singing a song for Botan. So she definitely played her rage up for the audience, even if she really is pissed.

社会人になり年月が経っていく中で、苦手なものは避け、当たり障りのない好物のみを摂取していく日々を繰り返し、気が付けば怒ることも泣くことも無く、ただフラットな感情のまま漠然とした日々を過ごしていた私に、ここまで鮮やかな怒りの感情を見せて思い出させてくれた事に心から感謝したい。本当にありがとう、るしあ。

それはそれとして最後にとあるポーカーの名言を送りたい。

『周りを見渡してカモがいないのなら誰がカモなのかは明白である。』

author: Max2000
text:
@Ale, Roza's Goggles  First of all, i know that she's a human being, and that people can get angry, but Youtubers, especially Vtubers represent everything good about people, being cute, charming, funny, playing games!
Second, i didn't know that this was a part of her character, so i'm sorry for that!
Third, I always thought for some reason, that everytime someone at Youtube gets angry and rage-quits, they can be considered "toxic",  but probably because i just don't get, how society works, especially on the internet, because i have that kind of an authistic, messed up mind set, that makes me take things a little bit too seriously. The critics, the reviewers, the let's-players, the actors, the singers, the musicians, i like to listen to them and support them, until i get the mixed thoughts, because of the haters, the trolls, toxic people, the internet cancer, who are usually hiding among them!
Fourth, i've literally heard her crying, like she wasn't hating her rage, and that kind of thing usually makes me uncomfortable, when i realise that it's a little bit too "realistic"! Although, at first it was kinda funny, when i first viewed that animation made by that user, who makes these animations with vtubers, like that "doggie girl" saying "EEKUM BOKUM", who actually was a nice Vtuber, and it was kinda funny, and cute!
I guess sometimes internet can take a portion of faith in humanity, from time to time, but at least i'm still trying to keep my faith! 
Just sayin', it was kinda troublesome for me, just like the other times i felt disappointed in some Youtubers, and actors, etc. throughout my life... Anyway i can't really reply to anymore comments, 'cause it's late at night, where i'm at, so good night, i guess.

But maybe you have a point, i mean getting angry was probably just part of her charm, and it actually can be funny when i give it a chance. Anyway, sorry for the misunderstanding.
